steps.content:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": "{
  "database": "nyiso_db",
  "schema": "public",
  "table_count": 6,
  "tables": [
    {
      "name": "nyiso_actual_load",
      "description": "This table includes the actual real-time load across all the zones in the NYISO market region. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the load data. The corresponding utc_timestamp invariant of daylight savings. The 'Zone_name' column contains the zone names. The 'load_mw' column contains the load data in MW. 'is_forecast' reflects if the data is forecasted or actual measured data."
    },
    {
      "name": "nyiso_ancillary_services",
      "description": "This table shows the ancillary service prices across different regions in the NYISO market. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the prices. The corresponding utc_timestamp invariant of daylight savings. The 'Zone_name' column contains the zone names. The 'min_spinning_reserve' column contains prices for the 10-minute spinning reserve ancillary service product in $/MWh. 'Min_non_sync_reserve' column contains prices for the 10-minute non-synchronous reserve ancillary service product in $/MWh. The 'Min_operating_reserve' column contains the 30-minute operating reserve ancillary service product. 'Regulation_capacity' contains the capacity prices for frequency regulation ancillary service product in $/MWh. The 'Regulation_movement' column contains regulation movement prices in $/MW, which is also associated with the frequency regulation ancillary service product. 'Is_day_ahead' column reflects if the price data is for the day-ahead energy market or the real-time energy market."
    },
    {
      "name": "nyiso_counties",
      "description": "This table includes mappings of different zones in the NYISO market to counties. Columns: 'name' (the county), 'state'/'state_abbr' (the state), and 'zone_id' (references nyiso_zones.id -- join to it for the zone code/name). This allows users to get prices for each county based on the associated zone."
    },
    {
      "name": "nyiso_fuel_mix",
      "description": "This table shows the fuel mix at different time steps across the entire NYISO market region. The 'Fuel_category' column includes the name of each type of technology in the NYISO supply mix. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the fuel mix. The corresponding utc_timestamp invariant of daylight savings. The 'Generation_mw' column contains the actual amount of energy produced by each technology in MW. The 'Is_day_ahead' column reflects if the data applies to the day-ahead market or if it is real-time data. The fuel mix data applies to the real-time market only."
    },
    {
      "name": "nyiso_lmp",
      "description": "This table includes all components that make up the locational marginal price of electricity in each zone within the NYISO market. The timestamp column contains the timestamps associated with the prices. The corresponding utc_timestamp invariant of daylight savings. The 'Zone_name' column contains the zone names. 'Lmp' column contains the resultant energy prices in $/MWh. The 'Marginal_cost_congestion' column reflects the congestion price component of the total energy price in $/MWh. Higher values, either negative or positive, reflect significant congestion. The 'Marginal_cost_losses' column reflects the costs associated with losses in $/MWh. 'Is_day_ahead' column reflects if the price data is for the day-ahead energy market or the real-time energy market."
    },
    {
      "name": "nyiso_zones",
      "description": "This table includes the zones in the NYISO market. Columns: 'code' (the zone code), 'name' (the zone name), and 'description' (the full zone description) -- there is no 'zone_name' column. The zones provide geographical reference points for price data across different parts of the NYISO market region. These zones are also the hubs."
    }
  ]
}",
  "error": null,
  "metadata": {
    "method": "show_tables"
  }
}

